]]></description><link>https://www.pinkvilla.com/lifestyle/home-decor/inside-dhvani-bhanushalis-design-forward-mumbai-home-where-pastels-take-center-stage-1387894</link><guid  isPermaLink="false">pinkvilla-1387894</guid><pubDate>Thu, 15 May 2025 18:57:13 +05:30</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Ultimate travel guide to Spain’s Mallorca: KL Rahul-Athiya Shetty’s getaway in most affordable place in Europe ]]></title><description><![CDATA[<img src="https://www.pinkvilla.com/images/2025-05/867670848_spains-mallorca-kl-rahul-athiya-shettys-getaway-in-most-affordable-place-in-europe.jpg"></img><p><strong>Where to visit and what to expect?</strong></p>

<p><strong>1. Palma De Mallorca and Palma Cathedral for city vibes&nbsp;</strong></p>

<p>Before embarking on the beachside adventures and isolated destinations, do not miss exploring the touristy city of Palma. The capital of Mallorca, Palma, encompasses some of the best landmarks of the island. Especially, Palma Cathedral, which is a 13th-century Gothic building. With its old architectural charm, mindblowing history, and the world&rsquo;s largest rose windows, Palma Cathedral is a must-visit in Mallorca.&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>2. Cal&oacute; des Moro for the authentic Mallorca beach experience&nbsp;</strong></p>

<p>Cal&oacute; des Moro is a beach paradise in Mallorca. The sheltered inlets, called coves, the glittery golden sands, pristine waters, dramatic coastal cliffs lined with pine trees, and nature&rsquo;s symphony will surround you with its calmness. Your nature getaway at Cal&oacute; des Moro will remain engraved in memory for ages.&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>3. Cuevas del Drach for boating through breathtaking caves&nbsp;</strong></p>

<p>For an unparalleled excavation, visit Cuevas del Drach. Take a boat ride to a 170-meter-long trail that goes through an underground lake called Lake Martel. The mesmerizing caves encompass beautiful rock formations that will gobsmack and excite you at the same time. As you move forward, you&rsquo;ll find an auditorium-like space where a live concert takes place. With classical music, nature-crafted art, and an azure lake, you&rsquo;ll be in a total detachment from the cities&rsquo; hustle and bustle.&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>4. Valldemossa village and the Village of Dei&agrave; for exploring historical architecture&nbsp;</strong></p>

<p>A trip to Spain is incomplete without a stroll through its cobblestone streets. The Valldemossa village introduces you to its stunning landmarks, such as the Carthusian monastery and the Palace of King Sancho. These old Gothic buildings will tell you the tales of culturally-rooted Mallorcan architecture. The food and the local bakery shops here are worth relishing in, as you soak yourself in the place&rsquo;s cultural depth. Village of Dei&agrave;, a peaceful village, is located only a short drive away from Valldemossa, known for its picture-perfect scenery.&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>5. Es Pont&agrave;s Natural Sea Arch for a picturesque pic&nbsp;</strong></p>

<p>Es Pont&agrave;s Natural Sea Arch is one of the most picturesque locations of Mallorca. This breathtaking bridge-like rock formation, created by nature, will hypnotize you into staying a little longer. Enjoy the scenic view of Es Pont&agrave;s, aka the big bridge, visit with a boat trip, or if you&rsquo;re adventurous, relish in some cliff jumping.&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>6. S&oacute;ller and the Church of Sant Bartomeu for exploring Gothic town architecture&nbsp;</strong></p>

<p>To truly witness a full-fledged Gothic town architecture, visit S&oacute;ller and the Church of Sant Bartomeu. This beautiful town will have your heart as it will take you on a fantasy trip to vintage masterpieces. The Church of Sant Bartomeu holds an ethereal charm as it displays stone carvings, high-rising arches, tinted glass, and intricate interior designs. This is also a great place to socialize as people from all around the world gather here and indulge in the local food and drinks.&nbsp;</p>
