	<li>
	<p>The first step is acceptance. You need to accept that you have a crush on someone and that it is okay.&nbsp;</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>Don&rsquo;t lose yourself. Focus on yourself and prioritize your own mental well-being.&nbsp;</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>Develop a realistic viewpoint. Change your perspective and look at the situation from afar. You will soon realize that your crush is just like other people.&nbsp;</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>Don&rsquo;t idolize them. When we fall for someone we tend to put them on a pedestal, which leads to us overlooking their flaws.&nbsp;</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>Keep yourself busy. Distract yourself by focusing on work and pursuing your hobbies. You can watch movies, hang out with friends, or read a book.&nbsp;</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>Give your mind a break from constantly thinking about them. Don&rsquo;t let your feelings for them consume all your thoughts.&nbsp;</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>If you still find yourself hovering over his profile, it&rsquo;s better to stay away from social media for the time being.&nbsp;</p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>If you&rsquo;re committed to someone, try to focus on your current relationship. It&rsquo;s not something unnatural. But try to keep a respectful distance between you and your crush.&nbsp;</p>
	</li>
</ul>

<p>Crushes are momentary. When you have a crush on someone, your feelings towards them will falter with time. But on the other hand, if you notice that your feelings are only getting stronger, you might be in love with them. If you find yourself wondering &ldquo;How do I know if I have a crush&rdquo;, it&rsquo;s better to do your own research and be sure of your feelings, before you approach them. It&rsquo;s up to you to decide if it&rsquo;s just a casual crush or something serious. It&rsquo;s important to understand the difference between having a crush on someone and being obsessed with them. In the case of the latter, you can seek professional help. Try to divert your attention and distance yourself from the person in question.&nbsp;</p>
