<p>This is not about playing hard to get. However, you don&rsquo;t want to seem too available either as it does not make a great impression. Besides, you should allow her some time to miss you as well.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>2. Don&rsquo;t Make Her Wait Too Long:</strong></p>

<p>Having mentioned the above point, it is also important that you don&rsquo;t make her wait too long. This would make her feel that you&rsquo;re uninterested and eventually she&rsquo;ll lose interest as well.&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>3. Don&rsquo;t Send Lazy, One-word Replies:</strong></p>

<p>This shows a lack of interest, too! Besides, one-word replies can make you seem arrogant and deprive her of learning any good things about you, which would easily put her off.</p>

<p><strong>4. Don&rsquo;t Text At the Wrong Hour:</strong></p>

<p>Texting her after midnight or during busy hours of the day can seem annoying and inappropriate.&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>5. Don&rsquo;t Be Inappropriate:</strong></p>

<p>In the endeavor of flirting with her, ensure you don&rsquo;t make indecent or suggestive comments. This can creep her out and make her feel uncomfortable.</p>

<p><strong>6. Don&rsquo;t Make Insensitive Jokes:</strong></p>

<p>While humor is great, you should test the waters first to see what kind of jokes she is comfortable with. Don&rsquo;t be too sardonic or make caustic remarks that may seem too personal. Avoid sounding like a misogynist, racist, homophobe, etc. The idea is simple &mdash; just be a decent person. If opening with humor, make sure your jokes are not too political or touch upon any religion, community, nationality, economic strata, etc.&nbsp;</p>

<p>The above-mentioned texts to make her want you are perfect for getting a girl&rsquo;s attention. Whether you want to break the ice with a girl, keep a conversation going, or make your partner feel loved &mdash; these texts can help you express yourself better. You can also tweak or personalize these texts to add a personal touch and make the girl feel more special.&nbsp;</p>
